==Law and government==

Caracas tiene cinco municipios: Baruta, El Hatillo, Chacao, Libertador y Sucre. Le [[constitution of Venezuela]] specifies that municipal governments be divided into [[executive (government)|executive]] and [[legislative]] branches. The executive government of the municipality is governed by the mayor, while the legislative government is managed by the Municipal council. In [[March 8]], [[2000]], the year after a new constitution was introduced in Venezuela, it was [[decree|decreed]] in ''Gaceta Oficial'' N° 36,906 that the [[Metropolitan District of Caracas]] would be created, and that some of the powers of these municipalities would be delegated to the ''Alcaldía Mayor'', physically located in Libertador municipality.

